I might have been misunderstanding what the Add to Frontier was supposed 
to do, and in light of your comment it makes sense.  The frontier will 
be determined based on the original seed list in the case of a domain 
scope crawl, and adding a new URL to the frontier via Add to Frontier 
would be evaluated within that context, but adding them to the seed list 
would make them part of the frontier.

Am I understanding correctly now?

Thanks,
